metadata.name: The Last Dance
metadata.description:
It was the first time I’ve done a self-portrait outdoors and I wanted something special. In a lagoon lost in this magnificent country of Iceland, I had to cross the water coming from the glaciers, naked, and climb on the iceberg that I had spotted. I cut my feet and buttocks but I am extremely proud to have done so, and especially proud of the result.

The Last Dance - Photography  
Location : A lagoon in the Vatnajökull, Iceland  
Self-portrait, 2021.
